</blockquote>

My solution: I run my own DNS server, and have updated its blacklist to block the ad provider used here (r66t.com):

<p>

<blockquote>
<A href="http://maradns.org/deadwood/doc/my.current.blacklist">http://<![if gt IE 6]>&#8203;<![endif]><wbr>maradns.<![if gt IE 6]>&#8203;<![endif]><wbr>org/<![if gt IE 6]>&#8203;<![endif]><wbr>deadwood/<![if gt IE 6]>&#8203;<![endif]><wbr>doc/<![if gt IE 6]>&#8203;<![endif]><wbr>my.<![if gt IE 6]>&#8203;<![endif]><wbr>current.<![if gt IE 6]>&#8203;<![endif]><wbr>blacklist</A>
